<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 15 at 7:00PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern
Meriwether, southern Pike, northwestern Upson and north central
Talbot Counties through 730 PM EDT...
At 700 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Crest, or 7 miles
northwest of Thomaston, moving west at 10 mph.
HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, up to penny sized hail and frequent
cloud to ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Thomaston, Greenville, Manchester, Woodbury, Molena, Gay, Sunset
Village, Raleigh, Atwater, Lifsey Springs, Sprewell Bluff State Park,
Crest, Sunnyside, Hannahs Mill and Imlac.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
